eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Age requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: At least 18 years of age at the time of consent

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: cUTI signs and symptoms
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Presenting at least two of the following new, persistent or worsening cUTI signs and symptoms at screening visit: a) fever (temperature >38 degrees Celsius or >100.4 degrees Fahrenheit), hypothermia (temperature <35.5 degrees Celsius or <95.9 degrees Fahrenheit), rigors, or chills b) dysuria, urinary frequency, urgency, or hematuria c) suprapubic pain or pelvic pain d) costovertebral angle (CVA) tenderness e) nausea or vomiting f) radiographic evidence of pyelonephritis g) leukocytosis

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Evidence of pyuria
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Urine specimen with evidence of pyuria a) dipstick analysis positive for nitrite and/or leukocyte esterase, or; b) ≥10 white blood cells (WBCs) per cubic millimeter [mm3], or; c) ≥10 WBCs per high power field (hpf), or; d) clinically suspected pyuria (e.g. change in urine color, sediment in urine, or foul-smelling urine)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: cUTI requiring diagnosis and treatment
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Having cUTI that requires microbiological diagnosis and treatment as suspected by the Investigator

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Active UTI or high-risk population
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Presenting active UTI that failed to resolve on first-line therapy or identified as a high-risk patient population; *High-risk patient population include those who are elderly (≥65years), male, pregnant, having recurrent UTI (≥3/year), with underlying co-morbidities (e.g. diabetes, immunosuppression, or CKD), or with known functional and anatomical abnormalities of the urinary tract (e.g. stones, stents, recent instrumentation, indwelling catheters, neurogenic bladder, or PKD)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Urine sample provision
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Able to provide at least 8 mL urine at visit 1 and 3

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Sexual abstinence or condom use
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Willing to abstain from sexual intercourse or use condoms during any sexual contact until the End-of-Study (EOS) visit is complete

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Protocol compliance
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Willing to comply with protocol requirements, including availability for follow-up for the duration of the study

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Informed consent
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Unable or unwilling to provide written informed consent

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: English language requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Unable to read and write in English (surveys are not available or validated in any other language than English)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prior clinical trial participation
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Currently participating in or has participated in an interventional clinical trial with an investigational product or device within 30 days prior to the Screening Visit

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Chronic antibiotic use
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Currently on or chronic use of any antibiotics for any clinical indication, other than UTI (refer to section 6.3.)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Recent UTI antibiotic treatment
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Receipt of any dose of a potentially therapeutic oral or systemic antibiotics for the treatment of UTI within 48 hours before the study baseline urine is obtained

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Fetal congenital anomaly
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Pregnant women with known fetal congenital anomaly (e.g., genetic abnormality or major congenital malformation) based on antenatal ultrasound

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Life-threatening illness
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Any rapidly progressing disease or immediately life-threatening illness, including acute hepatic failure, or respiratory failure

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Investigator judgment
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Medical condition or other factor that in the judgment of the investigator might affect ability to comply with procedures
